Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveNollywood actress Tonto Dikeh has responded to the accusation made by her colleague, Ada Karl, that she’s owing her N80,000 from 15 years ago.
According to Karl, the N80,000, 15 years ago is equivalent to eight million naira in today’s economy.
However, Dikeh in a post on Instagram denied owing her colleague any money.
She claimed Karl helped her 15 years ago and if she wanted to be paid back, she should make a request.
Dikeh wrote, “I don’t owe you, Jack. 15 years ago, you helped a little girl(me) if you want payback, you say it. I am rich rich now.”
The actress also asked that Karl send her account details to her management. She wrote, “Thanks like I always say for looking out for me…You can send your account details to my management. Have a good life ADA.”
Karl on Tuesday had berated Dikeh for gifting diamonds to her former boyfriend, despite owing her for several years. The actress also claimed that Dikeh had bought shoes, clothes and gold worth N80,000 and in today’s money, it’s equivalent to N8 million.
